docs.lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — President Vladimir V. docs.abstract: The Black Lives Matter movement has offered a rare moment for the descendants of plantation laborers brought aboard ships in the 19th century to make their family histories known.
docs.snippet: The Black Lives Matter movement has offered a rare moment for the descendants of plantation laborers brought aboard ships in the 19th century to make their family histories known.
docs.lead_paragraph: MACKAY, Australia — Marion Healy’s great-grandfather Kwailu was just a boy when “recruiters” took him aboard a ship on a beach in the Solomon Islands. The destination was Australia, where, for meager wages, he would do backbreaking labor planting and cutting sugar cane for white farmers.

headline.main: ‘No Slavery in Australia’? These Pacific Islanders Tell a Different Story
headline.print_headline: Australia Doesn’t Call It Slavery, but It Was Very Far From Freedom
